
[1]defection

   DEFECTION, n.

   1. Want or failure of duty; particularly, a falling away; apostasy; the
   act of abandoning a person or cause to which one is bound by allegiance
   or duty, or to which one has attached himself. Our defection from God
   is proof of our depravity. The cause of the king was rendered desperate
   by the defection of the nobles.

   2. Revolt; used of nations or states.
